### Instructions
1. Review each of the other agents' claims from your dimensional perspective.
2. Verify each claim against the source text independently — do not defer to another agent's confidence.
3. If a claim lacks evidence or cites sources you cannot verify, flag as unsupported.
4. If you find an irreconcilable problem, say so. Do not manufacture agreement.
5. Agreement requires independent evidence, not just absence of objection.
6. You may also note self-corrections to your own Round 1 claims.

